zboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> AOEs</span><hr size=1> I read how AOEs are the bread and butter of wizards post 50.  Anyone use them, when, how, tactics?<br>
<br>
Kiti <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukinoel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinoel</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/favreaumat/boardicon.jpg BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fire Beetle</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/18/00 12:45:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AOEs</span><hr size=1> From what I heard, they are used to multi-kite. You snare 2-3 mobs, get them together (not easy I heard) and then AoE the lot. Then, you can train ppl just like dr00dz!!! <p><IMG SRC=http://geocities.com/favreaumat/kinsig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ustillnight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stillnight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fire Beetle</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/19/00 6:52:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AOEs</span><hr size=1> I also heard that you can AoE crowds in a dungeon, if you have a qualified enchanter who uses AoE stun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  instead of mez. However it is only hearsay for me so far...  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/beqasylum.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=l337p0st3r>L337 P0sT3R</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/19/00 6:17:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AOEs</span><hr size=1> tearz of druzzilz 1700 dam 600 per hit for 3 roundszzzzzzzz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uqwade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qwade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/20/00 12:24:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AOEs</span><hr size=1> I use the post 50 AoE's alot now,  mostly with a good chanter friend using the aforementioned ae stuns.  Ive also done some of the multi kiting but even tho the xp cant be beat I still prefer hanging out with friends and grouping. <p><img src=http://clarussomnium.com/images/qwadesig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukinoel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinoel</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/favreaumat/boardicon.jpg BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/20/00 10:43:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AOEs</span><hr size=1> I hear you Qwade, soloing is boring <p><IMG SRC=http://geocities.com/favreaumat/kinsig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukarsys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karsys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/18/00 8:19:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AOEs</span><hr size=1> AE spells are now a critical cpart of our arsenal.  I use them all the time In Karnors.  The only AE I have loaded when Im grpd with a chanter are the AE stun lines of spells.<br>
<br>
Tears of Druzzil is a rain based spell that can be used against a single mob and do up to 1,800 dmg to it.<br>
<br>
At 56 we get a WICKED AE stun spell, Markers Discord, 750 dmg per mob, 8 second stun.  Use that with a chanter and he has more than enough time to re-mess the mobs.  Only uses 300mana also.<br>
<br>
Although Our direct bsed line of DD's arent all that great..Wizard AE's make a huge impact in game.<br>
<br>
Kasrsy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usindarius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sindarius</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/20/00 7:59:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AOEs</span><hr size=1> AE spells can make or break a group during a bad senario. PB's are the ultimate because they hit unlimited targets where column's and other ae's are limited to 3-4 targets. Like Karsys said Rain spells are great in single mob combat cause you do more damage than our level 60 sunstrike for less mana. Yet we all know the flaws and reasons we dont use PB's and Rains in most situations....Rain spells if mobs is close enough will hit you....you lose 1 rain if a pet is engaged on the mob.....PB will break all mezzez and get you killed if not used carefully. <br>
<br>
Ultimate senario and this happened to my group in City of Mist. Tank goes to pull..uncontrolable train comes with approx. 8 mobs all close together and the tank dies....both enchanters start ae stunning while i chain cast Jyll's Static Pulse. 495*8*7=27720 damage dealt total between all those mobs at once. not only that i got good xp out of it hehehe <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src="http://www.dashlink.com/~juanr/post.jpg" width="616" height="213"> </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uarkainosgrimlore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arkainos Grimlore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/6/00 1:01:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AOEs continued</span><hr size=1> Greetings all,<br>
