<br>
The problem that I recently have had (at the castle in FM) is-<br>
tank runs into castle, pulls a tump/ door pop-<br>
group now has two mobs- I yell out don't snare, let me- hit bonds of force- opps another player has snared/ rooted one of the mobs- now the two mobs are too far apart for any real area damage.<br>
<br>
And if one comes at me- let me kite it- not really that much of a problem.<br>
<br>
So now there are two angry mobs going on and the tanks are freaking out.  I'm using more mana trying to DD to sep maobs and the healer is going nuts trying to keep track of the tanks.<br>
<br>
&lt;sigh&gt; <p>Faeadari Freespyrt <BR>
High Elf Wizard of the 35th season<BR>
<BR>
<img src="http://www.crosswinds.net/~raiyvenmoon/New1.jpg" width="250" height="113"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uxyntic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xyntic</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/28/00 5:58:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/nickelle/Xyn1sm.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AOEs</span><hr size=1> I always have Tears of Druzzil loaded when going into a dungeon.  Since the usual make up of groups I join don't always have pet casters, Tears is the way for me to do maximum damage with the least mana (if the bugger doesn't resist.)  You can't beat 3 waves of 645 damage PLUS the fact that after the 1st wave hits, you can start chain-casting your main DD spell.  This helps alot when trying to drop a mob fast.  That's 2,598 points of damage for 623 mana (4.17:1)<br>
<br>
AE Kiting is similar:  Pillar of Lightning.  Snare your 1st mob and go search for your 2nd and/or 3rd.  Get all 3 rounded up nice and tight the let loose and watch them drop. <p><font face="Tempus Sans ITC"><font color="#999999"><fontsize=-2>________________________</font></font></font></b>
